radiographic_examinations.findings: Sub cm hypodensities within the right lobe of the liver too small to characterize. The liver enhances homogeneously. The gallbladder is normal without radiopaque stones. A simple renal cyst is noted in the midpole of the right kidney. There is fat stranding in the right lower quadrant surrounding a dilated hyperenhancing appendix measuring up to 11 mm. No evidence of abdominal fluid collection or extraluminal air.
